A faucet aerator is a device that is used in common household faucets to increase [[water conservation]]. Level of increased water conservation will vary depending on the faucet, but can be as much as 60%. Energy savings programs exist in many municipalities that will provide these inexpensive items for free, or they can purchased at a local hardware store. 

